All this to say:
I like live action looney tunes movies and I think the newest one is a worthwhile addition to this weird series of movies that all feature the same group of characters. I hope they do even more, and keep expanding into new genres.

-OG Space Jam is the  worst easy. There’s only a very few kinda funny cartoon gags and fewer good character moments with the Tunes in the whole thing. Jordan has no motivation and his arc is silly.
The ending isnt set up or satisfying.
And the whole thing’s weirdly disjointed.

-Space Jam: A New Legacy honestly isnt far behind IMO. It has pacing issues and is of course stuffed with too many cameos. But even if all three have flaws in their execution, I think Lebron, Dom, and Bugs’s arcs are all genuinely compelling, and it led to some great gags idc.

-Back in Action is easily the best of the films focused just on the Tunes, in spite of some jokes that didn’t age well and some weird choices. It gets why The Tunes comedy works, and more importantly who Daffy and Bugs are as characters. It deconstructs and rebuilds both well.

Btw after rewatching all four movies I can confidently say 
-Roger Rabbit is the best. It’s not a “Looney Tune” movie exclusively but it tells a GREAT story that seamlessly integrates the toons into its world, themes, and story, while still celebrating each individual cameo.

No one actually requested elaboration but
The villains in all four live action movies featuring the Tunes are: a guy trying to destroy low income housing for a profit, an intergalactic theme park owner, just a CEO, and a content creation algorithm that basically runs Warner Bros. https://t.co/jA3eDDdLMV
